modules.description: This module implements buffered I/O operations over a flow, providing functions to read and write characters, strings, and buffers with precise control over data transmission. It works with `Cstruct.t` buffers and a flow type from the parameter module `F`, handling partial reads, line-based input, and output flushing. Concrete use cases include implementing network protocols that require framed or line-delimited messaging over connections like TCP.

This module implements buffered I/O over a flow, offering precise control for reading and writing characters, strings, and `Cstruct.t` buffers. It handles partial reads, line-based input, and output flushing, specifically supporting framed or line-delimited messaging over connections such as TCP.
